description: [PR Newswire] - CHERRY HILL, N.J., Dec. 20, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- More than two-thirds of Americans believe there's no place like home for the holidays – with 67.1 percent of those surveyed stating that they'd rather spend the holidays with extended family than at a resort with a partner or close friends (32.9 percent), according to the 2016 TD Bank Holiday Giving Report, which surveyed 1,502 U.S. respondents aged 18 to 65+ via Google Surveys. In fact, only around one third of respondents (36.3 percent) said they don't engage in any form of charity during the holidays. "I find it heartwarming to see how many Americans believe in giving back to those in need," said Michael Carbone, Regional President, TD Bank.
title: Two Out of Three Americans (67.1 percent) Would Rather Spend the Holidays with Extended Family than at a Resort with a Partner or Friends, Says TD Bank Survey

"A lot has changed over the past three months, even as the economy has advanced in line with our expectations," says TD Bank's Chief Economist, Beata Caranci.

description: [Reuters] - Toronto-Dominion Bank did not set out to change consumer habits when it offered its TD MySpend app in April. Canada’s second-largest bank just wanted to offer more information to customers who use their phones to check account balances. "The real-time nature encourages customers to change their behavior toward their financial goals," Rizwan Khalfan, chief digital officer at TD Bank, told Reuters in his first interview about customers using the app.
title: Red means stop! Banking app cuts customer spending

description: [PR Newswire] - RICHMOND, BC, Dec. 10, 2016 /CNW/ - Today, TD officially opened its ninth branch in Richmond located at Unit 1505 - 4777 McClelland Road in the new Central at Garden City shopping centre. As one of Richmond's newest shopping destinations and growing communities, Central now has the added convenience of a full-service TD branch to complete the shopping experience. The new shopping complex, bordered by Alderbridge Way, Garden City Road and Alexandra Road, is an impressive destination and is a one-stop-shop for a variety of stores and services.
title: TD opens new branch in Richmond at Central Garden City shopping complex
